Configure the Data Cloud Profile Related Records Lightning App

Use the Lightning App Builder to set up the Data Cloud Profile Related Records app to show records related to a unified profile.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To create and save Lightning pages in the Lightning App Builder:	Customize Application

The app is added by default to the profile explorer’s profile detail page. You can also add it to the Contact record home page in a connected Salesforce org.

Navigate to the Lightning page where you want to configure a Data Cloud Lightning app.
From the Setup menu on the page, click Edit Page to access the Lightning App Builder.
Add the Data Cloud Profile Related Records app to the record home page. If it’s already added, click the app to select it.
Select a data space. If Default is the only data space option, select Default.
Select a primary data model object (DMO).
The profile data is drawn from this object.
Wait while the unified individual link object is populated.
Select a related data model object. The app shows records from fields in the object you select.
Only objects directly related to the Unified Individual DMO are available.
Click Select to open the Select Fields window. Move up to 10 fields from Available to Selected, then click OK. Data from selected fields is shown in the app.
Select the icon to display on the profile related records app.
Save and activate the component.
